</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> &quot;Searles O&#39;Dubhain&quot; &lt;odubhain@*comcast*.net&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-07-19T21:10:00 </POSTDATE>
People cannot be intimidated from posting on Usenet by spammers. loonies,
bozos,hateful people and jus plain idiots if they use killfiles to block the
garbage and insanity.

Killfiles can be loaded more quickly and efficiently than bozos can change
identities or make obnoxious postings.

As far as I know, I'm the only member of the Summerlands staff that posts
regularly to alt.religion.druid. The others have better things to do with
their time.

I post here to meet new people; to on the rare occasion discuss matters of
Druid religion and tradition and to not leave a newsgroup that I've served
since before it was founded.

Summerlands is a friendly Celtic Pagan sort of cyber-place. It's not a cult
but it is spiritual and religious.

Everyone who agrees with me is not a member of a cult. Some of these people
have very astute and strong minds.

Everything I post does not have a hidden meaning for the people who are
certain that it does. :-)

I don't think the gods are people or even necessarily human-like, contrary
to what one person goes on and on about. I do think the gods are spirits
that can inhabit bodies or anything else they so desire. They are
shapechangers in that respect but don't have to have a body to effect their
purposes here. In fact, their will is better worked on us from another place
not in this world but that contains this world within it.

I'm not making money off of being here but it would not hurt my feelings or
my principles if I did.

I don't want to be a Druid Pope or an Arch-Druid. I've turned down such
things when offered on many occasions. I do expect to be the master of my
selves and my many skills. I hope to acquire a greater mastery as I continue
doing the work of the Cauldron of Vocation.

I don't read anything by Dan, Dana, Jim or Root if I can help it as they
don't post on subjects that concern actual Druid religion or traditions and
frequently are just baiting me or other people when they do post (but not
always, but I don't really care any more).

I may not post as often to this newsgroup in the near future because I'm
doing some Druid work elsewhere, but I haven't given up on it, am not the
least bit intimidated by anything said to me or about me here, and am not
hiding from anyone. I'm right here in plain sight though I *AM* ignoring
some people.

I was a part of the petition that established this newsgroup in its very
beginnings and I'll not leave it because some people have behavior problems.
I like the idea of Druid religion too much to abandon its newsgroup.

I love alt.religion.druid. It's a part of my life and also a part of the
Druid way whether others know that, like that or want to change that fact.

Alt.religion.druid will prosper because of Druids and it will not fall or
fail because of those who attack it.

Is mise le meas,

Searles O'Dubhain
